  "local_port": 60516,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I'm broke and lonely. Tomorrow everybody is going to celebrate New Year's. Everybody is going somewhere with friends, families and girlfriends. I do not have the money to even eat something good and no one to celebrate with. What should I do?",
  "response": "I\u2019m really sorry you\u2019re feeling this way. It\u2019s tough to be alone and struggling, especially during times when it feels like everyone else is celebrating. But remember, you\u2019re not alone in this experience, and there are ways to make the day meaningful and even enjoyable, even in tough circumstances. Here are some ideas:\n\n### 1. **Reach Out Somehow**\n   - **Call or message someone**: Even if you don\u2019t have plans, reaching out to an old friend, family member, or even a coworker can help you feel less alone. A simple \u201cHappy New Year\u201d can open the door to a connection.\n   - **Join online communities**: There are many forums, chat groups, or social media communities where people who feel the same way gather. You might find companionship there.\n\n### 2. **Create a Simple Celebration for Yourself**\n   - **Cook or prepare something special**: Even with limited resources, you can make a simple but comforting meal with what you have. A warm bowl of soup or a favorite snack can feel celebratory.\n   - **Reflect and set intentions**: Use the time to think about the year ahead. Write down small, achievable goals or things you\u2019re excited about. It\u2019s a way to look forward with hope.\n   - **Watch something uplifting**: If you have access to the internet or a TV, choose a movie, show, or even YouTube videos that make you laugh or feel inspired.\n\n### 3. **Volunteer or Help Others**\n   - If there\u2019s a local shelter, food bank, or community center, volunteering can be a meaningful way to spend the day. Helping others can also help you feel connected and purposeful.\n\n### 4. **Go for a Walk or Spend Time Outside**\n   - A change of scenery can do wonders for your mood. If the weather allows, take a walk, sit in a park, or just enjoy the fresh air. It\u2019s a way to clear your mind and feel more grounded.\n\n### 5. **Practice Self-Kindness**\n   - It\u2019s okay to feel lonely or sad\u2014those emotions are valid. Treat yourself with the same kindness you\u2019d show a friend in your situation. You\u2019re doing the best you can, and that\u2019s enough.\n\n### 6. **Look for Free Local Events**\n   - Some communities host free New Year\u2019s events, concerts, or gatherings. Check online or in local groups to see if there\u2019s something nearby you can join.\n\n### 7. **Remember This is Just One Day**\n   - The pressure to have a \u201cperfect\u201d New Year\u2019s celebration can feel overwhelming, but it\u2019s just one day. The New Year is about new beginnings, and you have the whole year ahead to create positive changes.\n\nYou\u2019re stronger than you realize for facing this, and things can and will get better. Wishing you a peaceful and hopeful start to your New Year. \ud83c\udf1f",
  "temperature": 1.0,
